  - q: "How old is the Chinese lion dance?"
    a: "The lion dance dates to at least the Han Dynasty (206 BCE–220 CE). The earliest clear literary reference appears in the Tang Dynasty, where it was performed at court celebrations. By the Song Dynasty, lion dance had become a widespread folk performance at temple fairs and festivals."
